The paper deals with the complexity of local search for the Boolean constraint satisfaction problem (CSP), which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also uses a Schaefer-style dichotomy result to classify the complexity of such problems. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
